    narr:narration """This hub collects per-document **register assessments** under one rubric dimension across the corpus. The dominant reading is a [conversational-authoritative blend](narr:RubricAssess_register): direct, second-person address, active-voice dominance, and technical precision without jargon overload — surfaced in the [GTM strategic memo](narr:RubricAssess_Register_GTM), the [consulting pitch](narr:Assessment_Register_1), the [IP-crisis strategic piece](narr:Assessment_Register_IPCrisis), and the [the customer's chief architect enterprise assessment](narr:Assessment_Register_CustomerArchitect). But register is read as document-dependent, not uniform. A formal-technical cluster sits apart: the [architecture-doc assessment](narr:Assess_Register_cm) marks an authoritative tone with no casual markers, the [collective-memory doc](narr:Assess_Register_collective_memory) clear structured formality, and [ADR-001](narr:RubricAssess_Register_ADR001) a formal business register with first-person plural. Against that, the [founder/visionary material](narr:RubricAssess_Register) pushes to elevated and profane extremes, and [one assessment](narr:RubricAssess_Register_1) flags fillers as formality-reducing. The span runs architecture docs and ADRs through strategic memos to founder voice memos — recognizable as register-fit judgments, not a single verdict.""" ;
